name: Medvedev
summary: In the 2024 Wimbledon Championships, Daniil Medvedev defeated Jannik Sinner in a thrilling five-set quarterfinal match, setting up a rematch with Carlos Alcaraz in the semifinals. Medvedev triumphed despite a medical timeout for Sinner, who nevertheless displayed resilience in a four-hour marathon. Medvedev's victory highlighted his ruthless determination, while Sinner's exit dashed his hopes for a maiden Wimbledon title. The match also witnessed Medvedev's contentious interactions with spectators and his imitation of Novak Djokovic's signature gesture. The quarterfinal round also saw Alcaraz advance to the semifinals after defeating Tommy Paul, while the No.5 seed struggled to maintain score accuracy in his four-set win over Alexandre Muller.

summary: In the 2024 Wimbledon Championships, Croatian Donna Vekic defeated Chinese qualifier Lulu Sun in a thrilling quarterfinal match. Vekic's victory was marred by an incident during the match where she angrily shouted at her coach, prompting speculation about the dynamics of their relationship. Meanwhile, Jasmine Paolini awaits Vekic in the semifinals, having secured her place with a quickfire victory over another opponent.

summary: The film "Longlegs" has received mixed reviews from critics, with some praising its disturbing atmosphere and Nicolas Cage's performance, while others finding it disappointing. The Evening Standard criticized the film as "a disappointing horror" that "even Nic Cage can't save," while Variety praised Cage's performance in the "dread-filled serial killer thriller." Screen International called the film "flawed but creepy" and "a very weird, very upsetting, thoroughly captivating horror show," according to Nerdist. JoBlo.com found "Longlegs" to be "a very unique and unsettling experience," while the BBC called it "this summer's great 'anti-blockbuster.'" Awards Radar hailed the film as "a serial killer horror masterpiece that burrows deep within your psyche."

name: Shirley Bassey
summary: Legendary singer Dame Shirley Bassey has been bestowed with a prestigious honor by King Charles III at Windsor Castle. The 87-year-old icon received a Dame Commander of the Order of the British Empire (DBE) award, recognizing her remarkable contributions to the music industry. Despite her prior experience performing for the king, Bassey admitted that receiving the honor directly from him was more nerve-racking. Breaking royal protocol, Bassey inadvertently extended her hand to shake the King's, eliciting a brief moment of surprise. Nonetheless, Bassey expressed her deep humility and gratitude for the recognition, stating that she values her family above all else.

summary: In the 2024 Wimbledon tournament, Jasmine Paolini has emerged as a standout performer. Paolini's success has garnered significant attention, with media outlets highlighting her exceptional skills and determination. Despite Madison Keys' withdrawal from their match due to injury, Paolini's spirit and perseverance have been widely praised. Donna Vekic, who overcame personal challenges to reach the semi-finals, will now face Paolini in an anticipated match-up. Paolini's rise in the tennis world has made her a player to watch, and her performances at Wimbledon have cemented her status as a rising star.

name: Lindsay Hoyle
summary: In the recent general election in Chorley, Sir Lindsay Hoyle successfully retained his seat in the House of Commons. Following the election, Hoyle was re-elected as Speaker of the House of Commons, a highly visible role in which he presides over debates and maintains order in the chamber. As Speaker, Hoyle plays a crucial role in upholding parliamentary standards and procedures. Despite the demanding nature of the position, Hoyle has expressed enthusiasm for the task and has previously highlighted his commitment to fairness and impartiality. Notably, Hoyle's re-election involved a centuries-old tradition of being physically dragged to the Speaker's Chair, symbolizing the reluctance associated with the responsibility.
